Hind and posterior tibiae slender, bearing short and robust hairs on its external aspect, long and thin on its inner aspect. Flight organs short, not reaching terminalia. Forewings 2.91 times as long as pronotum, hyaline, brown with narrow white strip on external anterior margin, distal margin rounded. Stigma concolour. Hind wings with costal and discoidal hyaline, anal area more or less infumated — this latter trait is particularly evident when wings are folded over the abdomen (
Fig. 7
).
